/**
 * styl/style.styl -> css/style.css
 * @guidelines: https://github.com/causes/scss-lint/blob/master/lib/scss_lint/linter/README.md
 * the above is written for scss, but most of the ideas and rules still apply
 *
 * also some things I do:
 * short is better than long for class and id names, as long as it's descriptive
 * ids are good and you should use them if an element is global
 * avoid regex, if possible
 * try to keep things alphabetical. selectors, rules, everything
 * keep files small, break them into multiple files as needed to keep things manageable
 * i prefer /** for comments longer than 1 line. use // otherwise. the compiler removes both.
 * mixins first, then extends, then styles
 * avoid transition all, use the custom transition mixin
 * class-name not className. i reserve the use of camel case for js.
 * do not use the data-js attr for styling. keep js and css separate.
*/

